found on the sea bed mostly in coastal waters
a small muscle on each side of the back of a fowl
edible body of any of numerous oysters

value.def: An oyster is a large flat shellfish. Some oysters can be eaten and others produce valuable objects called pearls.

example.ex: He had two dozen oysters and enjoyed every one of them.
example.tran: 他吃了两打牡蛎，每一只都吃得津津有味。

value.def: If you say that the world is someone's oyster, you mean that they can do anything or go anywhere that they want to.

example.ex: You're young, you've got a lot of opportunity. The world is your oyster.
example.tran: 你还年轻，机会有的是。世界是属于你的。

value.tran: 世界是属于…的；尽可做想做之事（或去想去之处）

trans: 生鸡蛋醒酒汤(用于解除宿醉)
